# 🛍️ ASOS Product Analysis

## 📌 Overview

This project focuses on analyzing product data from ASOS (an online fashion retailer) to extract actionable business insights. The goal is to understand product availability, pricing trends, and potential revenue loss due to stockouts using data analysis techniques.

## 🚀 Objectives

* Analyze product pricing and availability
* Identify high-revenue loss products
* Detect stockout patterns
* Generate insights for inventory optimization

## 🧠 Key Insights

* Identified top products contributing to revenue loss due to stockouts
* Highlighted pricing patterns across different brands
* Provided data-driven recommendations for inventory management

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib / Seaborn
* Jupyter Notebook

## 📊 Features

* Data Cleaning & Preprocessing
* Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
* Revenue Loss Calculation
* Visualization of trends and patterns

## 📂 Project Structure

```
asos-analysis/
│── data/                # Raw & cleaned datasets
│── notebooks/           # Jupyter notebooks
│── src/                 # Scripts for processing
│── outputs/             # Charts & results
│── requirements.txt
│── README.md
│── .gitignore
```

## 📈 Sample Analysis

* Top 5 products with highest revenue loss
* Brand-wise pricing distribution
* Stockout frequency analysis

## ⚙️ Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/asos-analysis.git
cd asos-analysis
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## ▶️ Usage

Run the notebook:

```bash
jupyter notebook
```

